Job  creation  and youth  empowerment  were  the  key  themes  tackled  at  the  Forum. The  Tony  Elumelu  Foundation,  which  has  been  at  the  forefront  of advocating  for  entrepreneurship  as  the  catalyst  for  the  economic transformation  of  Africa,  convened  the  2-day  Forum  on  the 26th  and  27th  of  July  in Abuja. At the Forum,  Tony  O.  Elumelu,   Founder  of  the  Tony  Elumelu reiterated  the  urgency  in  creating  jobs  on  the  continent  to  catalyse Africa’s  development. He said:  “Extremism  is  a  product  of  poverty  and  joblessness.  Poverty anywhere is  a  threat  to  everyone  everywhere,”  he  said. Elumelu foundation, UNDP sign pact to support entrepreneurs Elumelu : Solving insecurity requires combined therapy Osinbajo, Elumelu task African entrepreneurs on economic liberation Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin